postcontent:
Almost NIB Taurus TCP 380 (Model PT738) with less than 20 rounds through it.  I'm the first owner.  I bought it along with a Ruger LCP to compare them and choose which one to keep.  Both of them have worked flawlessly and it’s been a tough decision but the LCP feels just a little better in MY hand so I’ve decided to sell this one.

This is a polymer frame gun…very light and it’s easy to make it disappear in any pocket.  The Taurus TCP has one major feature which the LCP doesn’t have and that’s last-round-slide-hold-open. When the last round in a magazine is fired, the slide locks open telling you the mag is empty.

The TCP is an outstanding pocket-carry design with a very smooth trigger. Its light weight (10.2 oz.) with a comfortable grip makes it an outstanding concealed carry gun. It's easy to pocket carry and just disappears in your pocket or purse.  It’s identical in size to the Ruger LCP but feels a bit softer to shoot than the LCP.

The full package comes with everything that came with the gun from the factory: original box, Taurus locking system with keys, all paperwork, and the 6-round magazine supplied by Taurus.

I’ve also included an extra factory mag that I had purchased, plus I’ve added a Talon Grip for increased control and comfort.

The serial number begins with “870...” and ends with “E” indicating this is a very recently manufactured gun.  The Taurus lifetime warranty travels with the gun, not just the original owner. 

I prefer face-to-face transfer in east Texas (College Station/Houston general area) without shipping. Must be a legal buyer, 21 or over with valid TX driver’s license or permit.

If I don’t respond to your email immediately, it only means I’m at work and I’ll respond soon after I get home. If the ad is still up, the gun is still available.

Considering the extra mag and Talon Grip, my cash price is firm. 

Sorry, but I’m not looking for trades or low-ball offers. Thanks!

This gun by all inspections looks to be never consumer fired and is as new today as it was when it was made in 1985 and the only thing we see on this BOA is a very slight turnline as can be seen from the pictures. The box is a bit beat up but still contains the end label that is original to this gun. This revolver is a true collector piece and reserved only for the Colt collector that wants to own the Holy Grail of all Colt Snake guns. If you have been trying to buy a mint condition BOA, this is your gun and it will placed in the center of any collection once you own it. Like we stated, the current owner has been storing this BOA for over 21 years after he bought it 1994 and this is not one that has been sold and sold time again online.
